What is software testing?

A process used to identify the correctness, completeness and quality of software.
Used to check that a software system is defect free.

Why is testing important?

Software bugs can cost money and lives.

- Airbus 8300 (1994)
    - 264 dead

- Therach-25 radiation therapy machine (1985)
    - 3 dead
    - 3 critically injured

- Satellite launch failure (1999)
    - 1.2 billion USD

- U.S. Bank accounts (1996)
    - 823 customers paid 920 million USD (823 * 920 million)
